column8: The prop nut anode is in poor condition and will be replaced on the next service.The paint is worn through along the edges of the keel and rudder, thru-hulls and transducer. There are multiple layers of paint missing in a 3” x 3” patch extending from the grounding plate on forward starboard side. Small osmotic blisters observed on rudder and hull along the waterline.
Replaced prop nut, shaft on next service
Some paint chips missing along waterline, heavy growth starting in these areas. Will replace shaft anode on next service. Visibility very poor, may have missed a spot or two
Prop anode to be replaced on next service
